snippet.textDisplay:
And there goes down another fine musical masterpiece. Coke Studio being one of the finest places where different artists from different genres meet, it is a sad state to see the continuous degradation of the quality of the compositions. First Sayonee, then Ghoom Tana - both have severely let down and it really aches when I hear these studio versions, while the original songs gives goosebumps till date. And it's more saddening to accept the ongoing state since the most revered band from my childhood Strings is the producer yet the music just doesn't seem to be going right at all. :(

Clearly Coke Studio is gaining commercial success and stooping downwards. Hope there is some magic recreated like the past seasons and we don't have to remember Coke Studio as another musical journey that would forcibly push us into nostalgia in the near future.

Regards,
A sincere die-hard music fan
